==Walkthrough==
===Starting out===
''Items required: none''
{{Checklist|
*Speak to the [[Dwarven Boatman]]. ({{fairycode|DKS}} then go through the tunnel to the south west and through the cave entrance ) {{Chat option|1That's a deal!|1Yes, I'm ready and don't mind it taking a few minutes.}}
*Finish the conversation with [[Commander Veldaban]]. {{Chat option|2Yes, I will do this.}}
*Talk to [[Blasidar the sculptor]] on the east side of [[Keldagrim]], south of the kebab shop. {{Chat option|2Yes, I will do this.}}
}}

===Fit for a King===
''Items required: weight below 30 kg, [[Logs]], [[Coal]], [[Tinderbox]], 200gp, [[Law rune|Law]] and [[Air rune|Air]] runes to cast [[Telekinetic Grab]], 3 [[Sapphire]]s, an [[iron bar]], a [[redberry pie]], one free inventory space''
{{Checklist|
*Talk to [[Vermundi]], the silk trader in the eastern market. (Big building east side of river, silk icon) {{Chat option|2Yes, I'm looking for some special clothes.}}
*Talk to the [[Librarian]] in the north-eastern corner of West Keldagrim. {{Chat option|2Do you know anything about King Alvis' clothes?}}
*Climb any bookcase to find a [[book on costumes]] known as the 'Scholars Guide to Dwarven Costumes'.
**'''Note:''' '''If you weigh 30 kg or more, you will be unable to climb the ladder.'''
*If you didn't bring coal, mine in the northeast corner of East Keldagrim or purchase from [[Ordan]] in the [[Blast Furnace]].
*Talk to [[Vermundi]] again. {{Chat option|2Yes, about those special clothes again...}}
*Use your coal and logs on the spinning machine next to Vermundi then light it with a tinderbox.
*Talk to [[Vermundi]] again and pay 200gp for [[exquisite clothes]]. {{Chat option|2Yes, about those special clothes again...|1I'll pay.}}
*While here, steal from the baker's or crafting stall for completion of a task in the Easy Fremennik Diary (optional)
*Talk to [[Saro]] at the anvil south-west of the bank in [[West Keldagrim]]. {{Chat option|2Yes, I'm looking for a pair of special boots.}}
*Speak to [[Dromund]] in the house just north of the bank.
*Take the [[left boot]] when he isnâ€™t looking.
*Go outside behind his house and telegrab the [[right boot]] through the window when he isn't looking.
*Talk to [[Santiri]] at the weapon shop in north-western West Keldagrim. {{Chat option|2Yes, I'm looking for a particular battleaxe.|2Blasidar the sculptor needs it for his statue.|2Perhaps I can repair the axe?}}
*Use your 3 sapphires on the axe (now in your inventory) and talk to him again. {{Chat option|2Yes, I'm looking for a particular battleaxe.}}
*If you have not completed The Knight's Sword Quest then you must speak to the librarian and then to Reldo in Varrock Library.
*Talk to [[Thurgo]] at [[Mudskipper Point]] ({{Fairycode|AIQ}}), and give him an iron bar to repair the axe. {{Chat option|2Something else.|3Can you help me with this ancient axe?|1Return to Keldagrim immediately.}} ({{Chat option|2Can you help me with this ancient axe?|1Would you like a redberry pie?|2Can you help me with this ancient axe?|1Return to Keldagrim immediately.}} May need a redberry pie if Thurgo has not received one recently).
*You will be given the option to immediately return to Keldagrim; do so. {{Chat option|1Return to Keldagrim immediately.}}}}

===Halfway there===
''Items required: [[Exquisite clothes]], [[Exquisite boots]], [[Dwarven battleaxe]]''
{{Checklist|
*Once in Blasidar's house, talk to [[Riki the sculptor's model]] to give him the clothes, axe and boots.
*Talk to Blasidar.
}}
===Joining the consortium===
''Items required: various ores, various bars, Stamina/Energy potions''

'''Note:''' If you want this section to go quicker, choose a company closer to West Keldagrim bank or Blast Furnace depending on how you're obtaining  the ores.

Warning!: *Do not hop worlds or you will lose your progress!*
{{Checklist|Lazy tip: rather than go back and forth you can just fill your inventory with say coal, and get a new task before closing the dialogue until you get coal.

*Go to the upper floor of the market and talk to the secretary of any company except the red axe, yellow fortune (only for females) and brown engine (only for males). {{Chat option|3Is there anything I can help you with?}}. Ensure you perform tasks '''only''' for the company you choose, as the progress for each is separate. Buy the ores from [[Ordan]] in the Blast Furnace to save time.
*Offer to help them.
**'''Note:''' The secretaries require you to retrieve ores (cannot be noted). Be sure to read the dialogue to know what ores you need or fill your inventory with about 5 of each.
**'''Note:''' You can also fill up your inventory with one type of ore, and speak to the secretary to ask for a task. If they ask for another type of ore, just click on the secretary again without accepting. Repeat this until they ask for the type of ore you are carrying (this will often take longer than just making trips to retrieve whatever is asked)
*After a few (3-8) tasks, the secretary will let you speak to the director.
**'''Note:''' Don't refuse tasks, if you don't like the task click on the secretary again for a new task before closing the dialogue. Refusing too many tasks will gradually reduce your favour with them, and you will have to do more tasks to make up for it.
*Talk to the director and complete a few tasks. {{Chat option|3Do you have any more tasks for me?}}
**'''Note:''' The directors require you to retrieve bars (cannot be noted). Be sure to read the dialogue to know what bars you need or fill your inventory with about 5 of each. The dialogue closing trick from the secretary DOES NOT work here! Instead, click on the director before advancing the chat window.
*After a few tasks, the director asks whether you've considered joining their company or states that you don't need to be doing running errands for them anymore. Join the company. {{Chat option|2I'd like to officially join your company.}}
*Tell the director that Blasidar sent you, offer your support. {{Chat option|3Blasidar the sculptor has sent me.|1I would support you.|1Yes! Long live the <company name>!}}
*Go back and talk to Commander Veldaban west of the bank, he will ask if you want to attend the meeting. You may choose not to.
}}
'''Quest complete!'''

